WEBVTT

00:06.966 --> 00:08.884
<i>- Previously on</i> Reacher...
- The colonel's
promotion's going through.

00:08.884 --> 00:10.261
There's no way a drug operation

00:10.261 --> 00:11.595
that happened
right under his nose

00:11.595 --> 00:13.681
is gonna be publicized
in a huge bust.

00:13.681 --> 00:15.641
Operation Kite Runner
will be shut town.

00:15.641 --> 00:17.476
Mr. Reacher. Malcolm Lavoy.

00:17.476 --> 00:19.478
The people who
want this weaponry

00:19.478 --> 00:20.896
can never be allowed to have it.

00:20.896 --> 00:22.732
If they knew you were involved
in the shady dealings

00:22.732 --> 00:24.650
that created Little Wing
in the first place,

00:24.650 --> 00:25.693
you'd be indicted.

00:25.693 --> 00:27.778
I'm prepared to give you
whatever you need.

00:27.778 --> 00:29.488
Why'd you send us
to get killed in an ambush?

00:29.488 --> 00:31.657
Our head of security told me
to give you that address.

00:31.657 --> 00:33.492
- Not Tony Swan?
- No.

00:33.492 --> 00:35.286
He's the one trying
to stop all this.

00:35.286 --> 00:36.787
Langston is vicious.

00:36.787 --> 00:37.955
If I didn't cooperate...

00:37.955 --> 00:39.248
<i>things that he
said he would have</i>

00:39.248 --> 00:40.708
<i>done to my daughter.</i>

00:43.711 --> 00:45.212
I want you to run down that way.

00:49.508 --> 00:51.594
It's not always fair, kid.

00:54.180 --> 00:56.140
Hold on, Russo.

00:56.140 --> 00:57.516
- The girl.
- She's okay.

01:13.657 --> 01:15.075
All right, we need
to get you two

01:15.075 --> 01:16.577
out of town to somewhere safe.

01:16.577 --> 01:19.246
I take it Chad's house
was the one place

01:19.246 --> 01:20.372
you thought you
wouldn't be found?

01:20.372 --> 01:21.957
Yeah.

01:21.957 --> 01:24.668
Everyone I trust
with my life or anyone else's

01:24.668 --> 01:26.629
is already involved
in this thing.

01:26.629 --> 01:28.714
Even Finlay up in Boston.

01:28.714 --> 01:31.342
What about Roscoe?
You trust her.

01:31.342 --> 01:33.552
Who's Roscoe?

01:37.848 --> 01:40.601
She's a friend back in Margrave.

01:43.854 --> 01:46.440
Senator Lavoy knew
what happened down there.

01:46.440 --> 01:48.692
If he was able to find out,
Langston could have, too,

01:48.692 --> 01:51.111
and potentially track
Marlo and Jane to Georgia.

01:51.111 --> 01:53.405
Neagley, Dixon, was there
ever a time in your life

01:53.405 --> 01:55.241
when you had very little
attachment to a place?

01:55.241 --> 01:57.326
Digitally, via paper trail,

01:57.326 --> 01:58.452
even emotionally?

01:58.452 --> 01:59.954
It'd have to be after
the military,

01:59.954 --> 02:02.373
'cause the Army knew every time
we scratched our asses.

02:02.373 --> 02:04.583
A few months after
I was discharged,

02:04.583 --> 02:06.210
I went to Buffalo.

02:06.210 --> 02:08.504
Worked in-house at this
debt collection agency.

02:08.504 --> 02:10.172
Only lasted six months
before I quit.

02:10.172 --> 02:11.215
It was a dirty business.

02:11.215 --> 02:12.925
Did you rent
while you were there?

02:12.925 --> 02:14.802
Yeah. Private residence,
apartment over a garage.

02:14.802 --> 02:18.556
Good. No property records.
Landline?

02:18.556 --> 02:20.391
Just my cell phone.
Non-local area code.

02:20.391 --> 02:21.725
- Utilities?
- Nope. Included in the rent.

02:21.725 --> 02:24.812
Well, that's
pretty much perfect.

02:24.812 --> 02:26.021
Anyone there you trust?

02:26.021 --> 02:28.274
My landlord, Bob Lee.
Retired firefighter.

02:28.274 --> 02:30.609
Old-school Irishman.
Lives for his grandkids.

02:30.609 --> 02:32.695
Like that
he was a firefighter.

02:32.695 --> 02:34.321
They have a sense of duty
and honor.

02:34.321 --> 02:36.115
I slipped on ice
in the driveway once,

02:36.115 --> 02:37.616
knocked myself out cold.

02:37.616 --> 02:39.159
Mr. Lee found me, picked me up,

02:39.159 --> 02:41.996
drove me through a blizzard
to Kenmore Mercy.

02:41.996 --> 02:43.330
Guy was 70 at the time.

02:43.330 --> 02:44.748
I don't just trust him
with my life.

02:44.748 --> 02:46.667
He may have
actually saved it once.

02:46.667 --> 02:48.085
You think he'd do you a favor?

02:48.085 --> 02:50.671
I send him homemade soda bread
on St. Patrick's Day

02:50.671 --> 02:52.590
and he calls me every year
on my birthday, so yeah,

02:52.590 --> 02:54.842
- I think he'd do me a favor.
- Buffalo it is.

02:54.842 --> 02:56.302
Great,
I'll give him a call.

02:58.929 --> 03:00.514
It won't be forever.

03:00.514 --> 03:02.808
We just need to kill
a few more people.

03:10.024 --> 03:11.442
Who wants treats?

03:11.442 --> 03:13.944
There was a shitload of options
at the vending machine,

03:13.944 --> 03:17.197
so I kind of got
a sampler's pack there.

03:20.367 --> 03:22.161
What?

03:22.161 --> 03:24.121
Um, can we have candy

03:24.121 --> 03:26.081
or do we need to talk
about murder some more?

03:44.516 --> 03:47.061
That's the only Clark Bar.

03:51.565 --> 03:53.317
So, what's the plan?

03:53.317 --> 03:55.152
O'Donnell and Dixon'll
make sure Marlo and Jane

03:55.152 --> 03:56.820
get off safely.

03:56.820 --> 03:59.073
Neagley and I have business
with Lieutenant Marsh.

03:59.073 --> 04:01.200
Russo's boss?

04:01.200 --> 04:02.785
Russo confronts him
about being dirty

04:02.785 --> 04:04.620
and dies within hours?

04:04.620 --> 04:06.872
I'd say we have a lot
to talk about.

04:24.515 --> 04:26.642
Car's in the driveway.

04:26.642 --> 04:28.644
Decent chance he's home.

04:28.644 --> 04:31.355
I want eyes out here in case
any of Marsh's pals show up.

04:31.355 --> 04:32.523
Copy that.

04:32.523 --> 04:34.900
Reacher.

04:36.652 --> 04:39.655
A good man
died in my arms last night.

04:39.655 --> 04:41.949
Whatever you do to Marsh,

04:41.949 --> 04:44.034
make him feel it.

05:13.022 --> 05:14.523
Is that the going price

05:14.523 --> 05:16.442
of an honest cop's life
these days?

05:18.652 --> 05:21.155
You can try, but that
wouldn't be smart.

05:21.155 --> 05:24.825
Listen, I did not want Russo
to die, all right?

05:24.825 --> 05:26.785
They guy worked under me
since he was a rookie.

05:26.785 --> 05:28.954
That's why you
couldn't do it yourself.

05:28.954 --> 05:30.664
So you made a call.

05:30.664 --> 05:32.833
Just like Langston called
those bikers in Boston.

05:32.833 --> 05:35.085
Cowards like you never
like to get your hands dirty.

05:35.085 --> 05:36.545
No, it wasn't like that.
Okay, yeah,

05:36.545 --> 05:38.756
I told Langston
that Russo was onto him,

05:38.756 --> 05:40.507
but I didn't think
in a million years

05:40.507 --> 05:42.593
that they would kill him.

05:42.593 --> 05:44.094
I figured he's wise up
when they dropped

05:44.094 --> 05:45.679
a bag of cash at his feet.

05:45.679 --> 05:47.389
- Like that one?
- Yeah.

05:47.389 --> 05:50.392
- Who the hell wouldn't
take this kind of money?
- Russo wouldn't.

05:50.392 --> 05:53.228
And anyone who knew him as long
as you did would know that.

05:53.228 --> 05:56.023
So when you called Langston, you
knew exactly what would happen.

05:56.023 --> 05:57.775
Go for it...

05:57.775 --> 06:00.778
if you really think you can
grab it and fire before I do.

06:00.778 --> 06:03.238
Or you can tell me
what I want to know

06:03.238 --> 06:05.532
and use that phone
to turn yourself in.

06:05.532 --> 06:07.951
Prison's not a great place
for ex-cops,

06:07.951 --> 06:10.245
but it's better
than the alternative.

06:10.245 --> 06:11.622
Barely.

06:18.670 --> 06:20.672
Aah! Ow!

06:20.672 --> 06:22.925
You just used up
your last bit of goodwill.

06:25.177 --> 06:27.179
Ow.

06:27.179 --> 06:29.098
We know the buyer--
Mahmoud, Mason, Marino

06:29.098 --> 06:31.183
or whatever the hell
he calls himself--

06:31.183 --> 06:32.935
will soon come into possession

06:32.935 --> 06:35.646
of 650 shoulder-fired
surface-to-air missiles,

06:35.646 --> 06:38.315
and that he's due to meet with
Langston and a New Age engineer

06:38.315 --> 06:40.526
to get the Little Wing software
chips installed in the hardware.

06:40.526 --> 06:43.737
I need to know when and where
that meeting's taking place.

06:43.737 --> 06:45.572
I don't know what the fuck
you're talking about.

06:45.572 --> 06:47.241
Nobody ever said anything
like that to me.

06:47.241 --> 06:48.408
Ow, ow!

06:48.408 --> 06:51.578
Oh, God! God... Stop. Please.

06:51.578 --> 06:53.831
I swear I'm telling the truth.

06:53.831 --> 06:56.917
Langston hired me
to keep tabs on Russo

06:56.917 --> 06:59.086
and just tell him when
he got close, that's it.

06:59.086 --> 07:01.046
- Then I guess we're done here.
- No, no, wait, wait!

07:01.046 --> 07:02.923
Stop, stop. Um...

07:02.923 --> 07:05.342
Um, look, uh,
Grant-Grant would know.

07:05.342 --> 07:07.678
- Who's Grant?
- He's the guy
you ran over last night.

07:07.678 --> 07:09.304
- He's dead.
- He's not.

07:09.304 --> 07:10.931
Turn-turn on the news.
He's not dead.

07:10.931 --> 07:13.892
He's in intensive care
in Mount Sinai.

07:15.060 --> 07:17.437
See?

07:17.437 --> 07:20.107
Being an honest cop
isn't that hard.

07:20.107 --> 07:21.567
Just ask Russo.

07:21.567 --> 07:25.779
Oh, wait. You can't.

07:45.632 --> 07:47.384
We're square.

07:54.266 --> 07:57.144
Okay. No one's gonna be
looking for you in Buffalo,

07:57.144 --> 07:58.770
but if you guys feel like
you need to stretch your legs,

07:58.770 --> 08:01.315
even just for a block or two,
wear these.

08:01.315 --> 08:03.483
Pull 'em down tight,
low to your eyebrows.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.360
Small precaution,
big benefits, right?

08:05.360 --> 08:06.945
- Yeah. Thank you.
- Okay.

08:06.945 --> 08:09.448
Driver's got five grand
in cash in-pocket.

08:09.448 --> 08:12.034
That guarantees you a safe trip
to Dixon's friend's place.

08:12.034 --> 08:13.785
Okay.

08:16.872 --> 08:18.081
Okay, Jane?

08:18.081 --> 08:19.166
Yeah.

08:19.166 --> 08:22.419
This isn't gonna do.

08:22.419 --> 08:23.879
Well...

08:23.879 --> 08:27.299
You know, when my boys
started in T-ball,

08:27.299 --> 08:29.259
I had to teach 'em
how to break in a cap.

08:29.259 --> 08:32.888
And I know everyone thinks it's
cool to wear 'em straight brim,

08:32.888 --> 08:36.391
but I'm trying to bring back
the classic look.

08:36.391 --> 08:38.602
- You want to help me out?
- Sure.

08:43.232 --> 08:45.734
How's that?

08:45.734 --> 08:46.735
It's good.

08:46.735 --> 08:48.612
Yeah? Let me see.

08:48.612 --> 08:51.156
There you go.

08:51.156 --> 08:53.867
Okay.

08:53.867 --> 08:55.661
Hey.

08:55.661 --> 08:57.454
You're gonna be fine.

08:57.454 --> 09:00.207
Your mom, she's pretty brave.

09:00.207 --> 09:01.875
And the dangerous stuff--
that's over.

09:01.875 --> 09:05.420
So you'll be all right.
I promise.

09:05.420 --> 09:06.964
- Okay.
- Okay?

09:06.964 --> 09:09.341
There you go.

09:09.341 --> 09:11.510
Okay, well, uh...

09:11.510 --> 09:13.971
Typically, it's hard for women
to say goodbye to me,

09:13.971 --> 09:15.222
so let's get you girls
out of here

09:15.222 --> 09:17.474
before you get too attached.

09:23.480 --> 09:25.899
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

09:29.736 --> 09:31.863
Speed limit all the way, sir.

09:37.244 --> 09:39.288
You're good with the kid.

09:39.288 --> 09:41.123
Would've been
a good girl-dad, too.

09:41.123 --> 09:42.416
Ah, kids are kids.

09:42.416 --> 09:43.792
Don't talk to them
like they're idiots,

09:43.792 --> 09:45.836
usually pretty easy.

09:47.546 --> 09:50.090
You know, we got this.
Reacher, Neagley, and I.

09:50.090 --> 09:52.509
You don't have
to finish this out.

09:52.509 --> 09:54.970
What's that supposed to mean?

09:54.970 --> 09:57.973
It means you've got more
at stake than the rest of us.

09:57.973 --> 10:01.226
If you want, you can
walk away with your chin up.

10:01.226 --> 10:02.728
With my chin up?

10:02.728 --> 10:04.271
Yeah.

10:04.271 --> 10:07.107
Really gonna try
and pull that line with me?

10:10.277 --> 10:12.070
Aw, fuck it,
it was worth a shot.

10:12.070 --> 10:13.864
Yeah, let's get to work, buddy.

10:13.864 --> 10:15.615
Hooah!

10:17.075 --> 10:18.702
I know with
the training holiday coming up,

10:18.702 --> 10:20.954
some of you may have made plans.

10:20.954 --> 10:23.415
Those plans might have
included heading off base.

10:23.415 --> 10:25.459
- Not necessarily.
- What gave you that idea?

10:25.459 --> 10:27.502
But I just heard from
one of our sources

10:27.502 --> 10:30.172
on Operation Kite Runner.

10:30.172 --> 10:31.715
The big buy
is happening tonight.

10:31.715 --> 10:33.508
Hm. Where?

10:33.508 --> 10:34.634
Some abandoned,
military-owned land

10:34.634 --> 10:36.219
about five klicks
northwest of base.

10:36.219 --> 10:38.722
The overflow lot? Motor pool
guys used to go there to drink.

10:38.722 --> 10:40.140
With the DONSA
and everyone

10:40.140 --> 10:42.309
clearing out for the weekend,
someone thought

10:42.309 --> 10:45.354
this would be the perfect time
to offload supply.

10:45.354 --> 10:47.522
- They're wrong.
- Weren't we told
in no uncertain terms

10:47.522 --> 10:49.524
that there were to be
no wide-scale arrests,

10:49.524 --> 10:51.693
no conspiracy charges, just,

10:51.693 --> 10:53.362
you know, accept the fact
they were FUBARing

10:53.362 --> 10:55.238
our entire operation
and that was that?

10:55.238 --> 10:58.033
Yes. That's what we were told.

10:58.033 --> 10:59.826
As the longest
tooth here,

10:59.826 --> 11:01.912
I just want to make sure
you understand the ramifications

11:01.912 --> 11:03.872
of going through
with this, Reacher.

11:03.872 --> 11:05.374
I know them
inside and out.

11:05.374 --> 11:07.334
I know that tonight
will be the culmination

11:07.334 --> 11:08.960
of two years
of incredibly hard work

11:08.960 --> 11:11.463
by every member of this team.

11:11.463 --> 11:13.090
I know that defying
a direct order

11:13.090 --> 11:16.551
will permanently damage
and possibly end career paths.

11:16.551 --> 11:18.512
We may not be discharged,
but they'll sure as hell

11:18.512 --> 11:20.472
make us wish we were.

11:20.472 --> 11:22.057
Busted in rank,

11:22.057 --> 11:24.518
shit assignments in
the worst corners of the globe.

11:25.977 --> 11:27.354
But if we do this,

11:27.354 --> 11:29.981
we'll be taking out an operation
pumping thousands of kilos

11:29.981 --> 11:31.441
of heroin into the country.

11:31.441 --> 11:33.735
And we'll be making sure
the criminals hiding behind

11:33.735 --> 11:35.195
the name
of the United States Army

11:35.195 --> 11:38.073
know they can't do so
with impunity.

11:39.533 --> 11:41.118
I think that's an okay trade.

11:42.411 --> 11:44.037
But since I probably have

11:44.037 --> 11:46.331
18 hours left as your CO...

11:48.542 --> 11:50.502
...I'll leave you to make
your own decision.

11:51.503 --> 11:54.589
If any of you don't want
to be involved, I understand.

11:54.589 --> 11:56.925
I couldn't respect you more.

11:58.385 --> 12:00.011
And every one of you
are free to walk out of here

12:00.011 --> 12:02.597
right now with
your chin held high.

12:28.248 --> 12:30.750
Then let's get to work.

12:43.805 --> 12:45.849
They're here, Lieutenant.

12:48.935 --> 12:50.770
Hold on.

12:56.943 --> 12:58.236
Shit.

12:58.236 --> 13:01.114
Don't move! Hands out and up.

13:01.114 --> 13:02.782
On whose orders?

13:02.782 --> 13:04.993
Major Jack Reacher
of the 110th Military Police

13:04.993 --> 13:06.620
Special Investigations Unit.

13:06.620 --> 13:08.663
We have reason to believe
these vehicles have been used

13:08.663 --> 13:10.165
to transport
Schedule One narcotics.

13:10.165 --> 13:12.000
Kneel with fingers
interlocked behind your head

13:12.000 --> 13:14.002
while we conduct our search.

13:14.002 --> 13:16.379
- You don't have a warrant.
- This is
the military.

13:16.379 --> 13:19.299
We don't need a search warrant.
On your knees.

13:21.259 --> 13:24.262
You heard the major. Kneel.

13:25.514 --> 13:27.516
Let's go, sunshine.

13:28.517 --> 13:32.771
Neagley, Lowrey,
watch these soldiers.

14:05.136 --> 14:09.099
- Damn it!
- Perhaps you were misinformed.

14:22.112 --> 14:24.030
- O'Donnell.
- Yeah?

14:24.030 --> 14:25.407
Switchblade.

14:42.340 --> 14:44.634
Light...

14:44.634 --> 14:47.387
Got a patch on this one, too.

14:48.638 --> 14:50.223
Ditto that over here.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.395
They're on all of them.

15:01.526 --> 15:02.902
You're under arrest.

15:05.030 --> 15:07.449
My buyers might have something
to say about that.

15:07.449 --> 15:10.952
Cops! Light 'em up!

15:47.113 --> 15:48.948
Duck!

16:54.222 --> 16:55.890
Thanks, kid.

17:09.612 --> 17:10.989
Shit.

17:27.839 --> 17:28.757
Aah!

17:40.226 --> 17:42.687
- Everybody good?
- Yeah.

17:44.314 --> 17:45.940
- Yeah.
- You good?

17:45.940 --> 17:48.026
Got a runner.

18:08.213 --> 18:10.006
Aah!

18:16.012 --> 18:19.724
Oh, my G...
You broke my fucking leg.

18:19.724 --> 18:21.351
I broke the fence.

18:21.351 --> 18:23.436
The fall broke your leg.

18:26.064 --> 18:28.149
Shut up.

18:41.496 --> 18:43.706
I am starting to see the appeal

18:43.706 --> 18:45.708
of your minimalistic lifestyle.

18:45.708 --> 18:47.544
Never too late to join me.

18:47.544 --> 18:49.087
Can I bring my guitar?

18:49.087 --> 18:50.880
- Nope.
- I'm out.

18:50.880 --> 18:53.341
- Can't forget this, <i>hermano.</i>
- Mm?

18:53.341 --> 18:55.176
Oh.

18:55.176 --> 18:56.970
My lucky lighter.

18:56.970 --> 18:58.596
Oh.

18:58.596 --> 19:00.223
I am definitely

19:00.223 --> 19:02.058
hanging onto this

19:02.058 --> 19:04.185
to show your future wife.

19:04.185 --> 19:06.271
Yeah, well, you're gonna
be holding onto that

19:06.271 --> 19:07.814
for a hell of a long time

19:07.814 --> 19:11.150
because I am
unattached for life.

19:11.150 --> 19:12.902
Ah. Well, I just want to say,

19:12.902 --> 19:16.739
on behalf of all women
everywhere, thank you.

19:16.739 --> 19:20.660
Hey, I had these printed out
in case anyone wants one.

19:20.660 --> 19:23.162
You know, a kind of
sort of keepsake thing.

19:23.162 --> 19:24.581
There you go.

19:24.581 --> 19:26.291
Sweet. Thanks, Franzy.

19:26.291 --> 19:28.293
Yeah, yeah, of course.

19:28.293 --> 19:30.545
Thanks, sucker.

19:30.545 --> 19:32.630
- Lose it.
- Yeah.

19:40.597 --> 19:42.056
Thanks, boss.

19:42.056 --> 19:43.892
Won't be your boss for long.

19:43.892 --> 19:46.102
Well, I guess I'm gonna
have to savor it while it lasts.

19:46.102 --> 19:48.396
Who knows when we're gonna
see each other again?

19:48.396 --> 19:50.481
Why would anyone
want to see these clowns?

19:50.481 --> 19:52.150
Wasn't talking about them.

19:53.735 --> 19:55.945
Oh, here we go.

19:55.945 --> 19:57.655
"Free Bird," extended version.

19:57.655 --> 20:00.909
Hell, no. You know the rules.

20:00.909 --> 20:03.786
But I got something
even better.

20:03.786 --> 20:05.204
'Cause we sure did go crazy

20:05.204 --> 20:06.706
on those sons of bitches,
didn't we?

20:15.840 --> 20:19.677
<i>♪ My love is the evenin' breeze
touchin' your skin ♪</i>

20:19.677 --> 20:23.723
<i>♪ The gentle, sweet singin'
of the leaves in the wind ♪</i>

